data.title: Revive Dental
data.meta_description: Meet our team of professionals, dedicated to providing a top tier dental experience for each and everyone of our patients.
data.text:
At Revive Dental, we understand that each patient is unique, and we take the time to listen to your concerns and tailor our services to meet your individual needs. From routine check-ups to advanced procedures, our team is not only highly qualified but also deeply compassionate, creating a dental experience that goes beyond the ordinary.

Dr. James Simpson, DMD

Owner

Dr. Jim Simpson was born and raised in Alexandria, where his office is located, he attended Campbell County High School before pursuing a Bachelor’s degree in Biology at the University of Kentucky, graduating in 2010. Following his academic achievements, he took a year off to explore and embrace different cultures, spending three transformative months living in Turkey and working in a dental office for six months.

In 2011, Jim commenced his dental education journey at the University of Kentucky, where he successfully earned his degree in 2015. His professional journey continued in Cincinnati, where he practiced at a cosmetic dental office, gaining invaluable experience in various aspects of dentistry. Driven by a passion for education and a commitment to providing exceptional services, he completed the implant curriculum in 2017 and obtained certification in clear aligner therapy in 2018.

Beyond the dental office, Jim finds joy in spending quality time with his dog, family, and friends. His passion for life extends to his interests in snowboarding, cycling, running, golf, and travel, reflecting a well-rounded and adventurous spirit. Jim remains dedicated to staying at the forefront of dental advancements to ensure the highest quality of care for his patients in the Alexandria community.

Dr. Michael Walker, DMD

Associate

Dr. Michael Walker grew up in Ft. Thomas, Kentucky and went to Highlands High School. He received his Bachelor degree in Biology at Northern Kentucky University, and attended the University of Kentucky College of Dentistry. After graduating from Dental School, he spent a year at The Ohio State University, completing a residency in Advanced General Dentistry. Walker has been practicing Dentistry in Alexandria for 32 years. Dr. Walker met his wife, Heather, at Ohio State. He has two daughters, Shelby and Alex, who both work at Cincinnati Children’s as nurses. Dr. Walker is a dog lover, and in his free time, enjoys golf, sportfishing, and spending time with family and friends.

Education:

-Undergraduate Degree: Nothern Kentucky University

-Doctorate Degree: University of Kentucky

-Advanced General Dentistry Residency: Ohio State University
